Pre-Game Insights: India’s tour to Ireland will kick off on Friday, August 18, which will mark the return of Jasprit Bumrah to competitive cricket following a year-long injury.
The Yorker specialist will lead the Indian side filled with youngsters.
The bilateral series will be played between August 18-23, 2023 at the Malahide Cricket Club Ground.
The home team will be helmed by Paul Stirling and will look to continue its decent run after qualifying for the ICC Men’s T20 World Cup 2024.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Prozeal Green Energy, Sterling Reserve and Kore Mobile have been onboarded as commercial partners by ITW Catalyst for the India tour of Ireland 2023.

The sports, entertainment and media consulting vertical of ITW Consulting, ITW Catalyst, as an exclusive rights holder, has managed to facilitate three sponsorship deals for the forthcoming India tour of Ireland 2023.

For the upcoming three-match T20I series, Prozeal Green Energy, Sterling Reserve and Kore Mobile have been onboarded as the front-of-jersey sponsor, non-lead arm sponsor and lead arm sponsor, respectively.

Paul O’Sullivan, Commercial Manager for Cricket Ireland, expressed delight in partnering with new brands Prozeal Green and Kore Mobile, and continuing the association with Sterling Reserve for the T20 series against India.
Paroksh Chawla, CEO of ITW Catalyst, highlighted the buzz created by the India-Ireland series and the confidence in helping brands achieve maximum exposure.
Shobit Rai and Manan Thakkar, Joint MD & CEO of Prozeal Green, emphasized the partnership's aim to raise awareness about environmental sustainability within the cricket community.
Bikram Basu, Chief Operating Officer, Marketing, Sales, Strategy at ABD India, mentioned the continuation of Sterling Reserve as a sponsor partner of Cricket Ireland.
Kamlesh Thakkar, Chairman & Managing Director, Kore Mobile, expressed excitement about extending support to Cricket Ireland through sponsorship.
